sql:
SELECT building_type
FROM buildings
WHERE year_built = 2000 AND units_res > 1000;

SELECT address, year_built, energy_efficiency_rating, water_efficiency_rating
FROM buildings
WHERE year_built < 1980 AND water_efficiency_rating >= 10;

external_knowledge:
- 'identity' in the metaphorical question refers to 'bbl' (Building Block Lot identifier);
- 'aliases' refers to 'building_name';
- 'tall structures' are buildings;
- 'conserved their energy' refers to having a low energy use intensity (EUI);
- 'vocal' refers to log entries or the number of times data has been accessed;
- 'measured footprint on nature' refers to the energy consumption measured by EUI;
- 'wise keepers of the buildings' refers to users with the role 'building_manager'.

sql:
SELECT building_name, energy_efficiency_rating
FROM buildings
WHERE energy_efficiency_rating > (SELECT AVG(energy_efficiency_rating) FROM buildings);

SELECT buildings.bbl, buildings.borough, buildings.year_built, buildings.occupancy_rate, energy_metrics.eui
FROM buildings
JOIN energy_metrics ON buildings.bbl = energy_metrics.bbl;

SELECT bbl, address, borough
FROM buildings
WHERE bbl = '0';

external_knowledge:
- 'High level of occupancy' refers to an average occupancy rate greater than 85%;
- 'Newer residential complexes' means buildings constructed after 1990;
- 'A couple of dozen' is commonly understood as more than 24 units, here specifically at least 25 units;
- 'Popular for viewing' indicates buildings that have records of viewing access in the usage logs.

- 'keepers of the keys to the castle' refers to the user roles;
- 'nature of the castle' refers to the building type as of 2016;
- 'energy consumption' refers to the energy use intensity (EUI);
- 'castle identified by '1'' refers to the building with the unique identifier (BBL) '1';
- 'those who can see or touch its walls' refers to the users with 'view' or 'edit' access type.

sql:
SELECT bbl, carbon_emissions
FROM energy_metrics
WHERE carbon_emissions > (
    SELECT AVG(carbon_emissions)
    FROM energy_metrics
);

external_knowledge:
- 'recent' refers to buildings constructed in 2010;
- 'sizable' indicates buildings with more than 10 residential units;
- 'energy-efficient' indicates an EUI below the 2020 average EUI.
